INDIA'S FIRST BULLET TRAIN CORRIDOR

The BEML B28 is purpose-built for the Mumbaiâ€“Ahmedabad High Speed Rail (MAHSR) corridor â€” 558 km of dedicated standard-gauge (1,435 mm) track stretching across Gujarat and Maharashtra.

This historic infrastructure project includes a 22-km underwater tunnel under the Thane Creek, India's first, and will run initial trial operations on the 46-km Suratâ€“Bilimora test section. Two B28 prototype trainsets are scheduled for delivery by end of 2026.

Train-B28 is engineered to operate in India's extreme climate range, from âˆ’5Â°C to 50Â°C, handling monsoon flooding, coastal salinity, desert dust, and high wind loads â€” a key differentiator from imported designs.
